                     Bureau of Transportation Statistics

                            Commodity Flow Survey

   The Commodity Flow Survey (CFS) obtains data on shipments by domestic
   establishments in manufacturing, wholesale, mining, and selected other
   industries. The CFS is conducted as part of the Economic Census by the
   U.S. Census Bureau in partnership with the Bureau of Transportation
   Statistics of the U.S. Department of Transportation.

